{"_id":"SRgoj9egHxYoN08A","name":"Snow Sorceress","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Miss Snow and Lady Storm","source":"Lost Stories","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a novice a powerful sorceress with limited power total control \nover cold and snow. My magic can come with dangerous, unintended \nconsequences cause small unwanted effects.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou can use magic to create and manipulate the \ncold. Describe the effects of a spell that has one of the following Keywords \nas a condition: Ice, Snow, or Frost. Y ou could, for example, Create an Ice \nBridge to cross a crevasse or Freeze an Enemy to immobilize it. Pay a cost \nof 1 to 3 Soma, decided by the Storyteller, to activate the spell. The effects \nyou describe last until the end of the Scene. The Soma cost is increased by \n1 when environmental conditions are not compatible with cold. Y ou can \ndecide to lower the cost of the spell by 1 Soma, but this will cause a minor \nmagical accident on par with an Outcome with a Cost.","notes":"Miss Snow and Lady Storm - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Miss Snow and Lady Storm","source":"Lost Stories"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"jwLtB80MCSCVx4ph","name":"Winter’s Kiss","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Miss Snow and Lady Storm","source":"Lost Stories","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am good at understanding dominating people. I have a unique \nability to comprehend their desires. I tend to distrust even close allies \ntrust those I don’t know.<h3>Gift</h3>In you lies the power of winter. When you give \nsomeone a chaste kiss, you can choose one of the following effects:\n1. Erase one of their memories. It must be the memory of an event in the \nScene in which you use this effect. Particularly capable Hunters and \nNPCs may require a Position Check for the effect to succeed.\n2. Make the subject immune to cold throughout the rest of the Scene. \nThis will prevent them from suffering frost Wounds and allow them to \nignore the effects of Lady Storm’s snowstorm.\n3. Make an object extremely fragile.","notes":"Miss Snow and Lady Storm - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Miss Snow and Lady Storm","source":"Lost Stories"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"IU3qpj84pEEFNg89","name":"Examine the Evidence","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Tremoteus Rumpel","source":"Lost Stories","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>My reputation precedes me, and my word is held in the highest \nregard by anyone with an ounce of honesty. I detest criminals and \nthose who act to harm the innocent. Big or small, a crime is still \na crime.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou can use each of the following effects \nonce per Scene: \n1. For the Record: Y ou can make a note of something a subject has said; \nyou will never forget it. Write it down because you can use it when you \nactivate your Dark Ego. By spending 1 Soma, the Storyteller will reveal a \nweakness of the subject whose words you have memorized.\n2. Consult the Laws: The Storyteller will reveal to you the customs and \nrules of a social group or place you are in. By spending 1 Soma, you \ncan create a loophole, known only to you, to the rules that have been \nrevealed.\n3. The Decisive Proof: When you examine an object, the Storyteller \nwill reveal a quality or feature that few people may notice. By spending \n1 Soma, you will learn who was the last person to own or use what you \nare examining.","notes":"Tremoteus Rumpel - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 4.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Tremoteus Rumpel","source":"Lost Stories"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"AWOtU7FX4aphctj0","name":"Your Honor","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Tremoteus Rumpel","source":"Lost Stories","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a keen disputant and have an uncanny ability to detect \ndeception. I need hard evidence before I’ll accuse someone of \ndishonesty.<h3>Gift</h3>If you stand in front of nobles, lawmen, or leaders in \ngeneral, you can spend 1 Soma to have them recognize your name or \nreputation. If you use your identity as a strength, you gain 1 Additional \nSuccess. If you give your word in a negotiation, you gain 1 Additional \nSuccess in a possible Position Check.","notes":"Tremoteus Rumpel - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 4.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Tremoteus Rumpel","source":"Lost Stories"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241686,"modifiedTime":1783973241686,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"DbfMHiJ5wScJsTOO","name":"Noble Birth","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Prince Trollo the Innocent","source":"Lost Stories","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a young prince, well-versed in the etiquette of the court. I \nam a diligent student, my favorite subjects being history and \npoetry. I am not ashamed of my strange appearance and I hate to \nhide from others.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene, if you are in a place where your family’s \nauthority is recognized, you can gain access to a restricted location, such \nas a dungeon or castle, or a direct audience with an authority figure. \nAs a prince, you have learned everything a future ruler needs to know. \nOnce per Scene, you gain 2 Additional Successes for an action in which \nyou can demonstrate your knowledge of history and poetry, or your skill \nwith the sword. \nI learned kindness from my mother and firmness from my father.","notes":"Prince Trollo the Innocent - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 6.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Prince Trollo the Innocent","source":"Lost Stories"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XmlhJpGB4Y05g2uH","name":"Good Heart","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Prince Trollo the Innocent","source":"Lost Stories","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I use these qualities to uphold the good name of my family. I will \nnot allow anyone to violate the ideals of justice and courage with \nwhich I was raised.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou have the innocence and strength of a true ruler.","notes":"Prince Trollo the Innocent - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 6.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Prince Trollo the Innocent","source":"Lost Stories"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"watwrGEFul8VNoKC","name":"Lost Childhood","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Pietrik and the Cauldron Fae","source":"Lost Stories","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I fear nothing and throw myself into any situation. The \nadrenaline of risk drives me to succeed. I get bored easily in \nsituations where there is no danger.<h3>Gift</h3>Despite your young age, you have no qualms about \ntaking action against enemies. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success in all \nactions that require the use of subterfuge. If you attack a target that is \nunaware of your presence, you inflict 1 Additional Wound.","notes":"Pietrik and the Cauldron Fae - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 8.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Pietrik and the Cauldron Fae","source":"Lost Stories"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"7swdUYywOetZGlZx","name":"Fearless","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Pietrik and the Cauldron Fae","source":"Lost Stories","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>The Cauldron Fae is always with me, in the form of a small \nfloating light. Her magic is still powerful, and I often summon \nher to wreak havoc or play tricks on humans.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou are immune to any fear or mind control effects that \nprevent you from acting as you wish. If you suffer 1 Wound from an \nOpponent or Threat, you may regain 1 Soma in your next action and \nmay consider a Failure as an Outcome with a Cost.","notes":"Pietrik and the Cauldron Fae - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 8.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Pietrik and the Cauldron Fae","source":"Lost Stories"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"55PhoLrc2WHrJTA6","name":"Thousand Faces","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Loki the Deceiver","source":"Lost Stories","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a skilled acrobat, I tell stories, perform magic tricks, and put \nmy audience in a good mood. I enjoy chaos and adding confusion \nto situations is a way for me to bring balance to the world.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene, you can assume the identity of \nanother Hunter. Choose a Hunter’s Sheet that no one is using and use it \nfor the rest of the Scene. Y ou have access to all the Gifts and abilities on \nthe Sheet, with the exception of the Soma points and Wounds, which you \nwill keep from Loki’s Sheet. Even though you have their likeness, you are \nnot the Hunter you are impersonating, so you do not know their personal \nhistory and cannot activate the Special Scenario Gifts associated with \nthem. Any effects of the Gifts you activate while impersonating another \nHunter will end when you return to your true identity or at the end of \nthe Scene. If someone discovers who you really are, your masquerade \nends and you take 1 Wound. If you wish, you can return to your original \nappearance before the end of the Scene. If you discover a deception and \ndo nothing to expose it, you gain 1 Soma.","notes":"Loki the Deceiver - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 10.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Loki the Deceiver","source":"Lost Stories"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"afGnf3qRsdTBfCJm","name":"Trickster","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Loki the Deceiver","source":"Lost Stories","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a master at distorting and unraveling deception. Verbal \nand body language hold no secrets for me. I don’t like to get my \nhands dirty and would rather have someone else do it for me.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou get 2 Additional Successes if you use your skills as \nan entertainer to perform an action. This includes polite conversation, \nsleight of hand, or performing stunts. Once per Scene, if you help an \nenemy (for example as a Cost), you gain 1 Soma.","notes":"Loki the Deceiver - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 10.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Loki the Deceiver","source":"Lost Stories"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"TDr3XfSGzLjUwZC8","name":"Legacy","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Silent Mother","source":"Lost Stories","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am able to understand the potential of young women and know \nhow to guide their steps to develop their true potential. I consider \neach of my protégés a true daughter and would give my life to \nsave them.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou can use all the resources you have accumulated from \nyour many marriages of convenience. Y ou can use each of these effects \nonce per Scenario:\n1. A Family Asset: Y ou can bring a large property into play, such as \na mansion or business. Y ou have free access to the property and its \nresources.\n2. A Family Friend: Y ou can introduce a Minor NPC who has a debt or \npartnership agreement with your family. The Storyteller will sketch the \nNPC, who will be well-disposed towards you.\n3. A Family Treasure: Y ou can bring into play a rare and valuable item \nthat you own as a family heirloom.","notes":"The Silent Mother - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 12.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"The Silent Mother","source":"Lost Stories"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"TmNZkCFMPbuQ8vLO","name":"My Beloved Daughters","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Silent Mother","source":"Lost Stories","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Although I appear helpless, I am a capable spy who knows how to \ndefend herself in dangerous situations. I never miss an opportunity \nto accumulate wealth and resources.<h3>Gift</h3>Two young girls you saved from an \nunfortunate fate follow you on your adventures. Y our adopted \ndaughters are two Minor NPCs with the following profiles:\nOL Medium 5 - (1 Wound)\nDecide on their names and stories, and work with the Storyteller to \ncreate a Descriptor for each of them that describes their abilities. Y our \nadopted daughters cannot have magical abilities or more than a good \neducation in their chosen discipline. Y our daughters will do their best to \nserve you at every opportunity.","notes":"The Silent Mother - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 12.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"The Silent Mother","source":"Lost Stories"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"H4uTQc0HHnvHSjaN","name":"Monk","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Karasu Kuroi the Wandering Monk","source":"Lost Stories","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am an exorcist monk. My body is tempered by a lifetime of asceticism \nand fighting evil spirits. I do not tolerate blasphemy and those who use \nknowledge for personal gain.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou can spend 1 Soma to activate a piece of your Spirit Hunter \nEquipment:\n1. Pastoral Shakujo: Banging your staff on the ground can temporarily \ninterrupt the effect of a spell or curse. The duration of the interruption (set by \nthe Storyteller) can vary from a few moments to the entire Scene, depending \non the power of the spell.\n2. Hauchiwa Fan: With a fan blast, you can make a leap of up to ten meters \nforward or upward. Y ou can use this effect on an ally.\n3. Tengu-gui Mask: Y ou can wear your mask to change your facial features, taking on a physical appearance appropriate to the context. Create a \nDescriptor that represents your appearance, but remember that you cannot \nreplicate the features of a specific subject. When you activate a Gift or suffer 1 \nWound, you will revert to your original appearance. \nThe use of this Gift is limited by the possession of the corresponding \nEquipment: if you lose an item, you cannot use the relevant option until you \nrecover it. During an Interlude, you recover any missing Equipment.","notes":"Karasu Kuroi the Wandering Monk - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 14.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Karasu Kuroi the Wandering Monk","source":"Lost Stories"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"bQadkOthDVaWAoQW","name":"Moral Rigor","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Karasu Kuroi the Wandering Monk","source":"Lost Stories","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Prayer keeps my mind steadfast and my words are an inspiration to \nthose who have faith. I do not tolerate the concepts of faith and \ndevotion being questioned.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou demonstrate righteousness in word and deed. Y ou gain \n1 Additional Success on all Position Checks where you make a commitment \nby giving your word as a guarantee. By spending 1 Soma, you can make \nmental contact with a subject present in the Scene who must accept the link.","notes":"Karasu Kuroi the Wandering Monk - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 14.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Karasu Kuroi the Wandering Monk","source":"Lost Stories"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"PTJ17IImOJCT2s4w","name":"The Team","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The 7 Hessian Mercenaries","source":"Lost Stories","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>We are experienced mercenaries and have seen every battlefield. We \nhate working for free and any chance to bring home some extra loot is \ngood.<h3>Gift</h3>At the beginning of each Scene, you choose the 3 members \nof the Main Team. Y ou will receive the 3 Gifts and the Special Equipment of \nthe members you have chosen. The other 4 dwarves form the Support Team. \nThe Main Team acts as a single Hunter and receives 1 Penalty to Checks for \neach team member not present in a Scene. Wounds are also cumulative for all \nmembers, and any member can act until the Team takes its last Wound. During \na Scene, you can spend 1 Soma to swap a Main Team member for a Support \nTeam member.","notes":"The 7 Hessian Mercenaries - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 16.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"The 7 Hessian Mercenaries","source":"Lost Stories"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"MrMN1RD6UDrDLZVb","name":"On Mission","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The 7 Hessian Mercenaries","source":"Lost Stories","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>We are adept at getting things, information, people, or anything you \nwant - ask and we will find it. We are intolerant of authority and \nanything with a hierarchy of command.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene, you can send the Support Team on a mission \nto accomplish a goal, such as capturing an NPC, discovering information, or \nanything else you deem useful. The Storyteller sets the OL of the mission just \nlike a normal Position Check. To find out what happens, you must make a \nPosition Check, where you get 1 Base Success for each Support Team Member \n(usually 4), but you cannot spend Soma to get Additional Successes. Depending \non the result:\nFailure: The objective was missed, and one of the team members is out of the \ngame for the rest of the Scenario. Describe what happened in the words of the \nreturning teammates. If the story makes at least one other Player laugh, you will \nrecover 1 Soma.\nOutcome with a Cost: The goal was completed, but there were problems. The \nStoryteller describes how it went and suggests a complication.\nStandard Outcome: Goal completed, no problems.","notes":"The 7 Hessian Mercenaries - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 16.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"The 7 Hessian Mercenaries","source":"Lost Stories"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"6gOWYlT1IMIOyfjK","name":"Pharmaka","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Circe the Alchemist","source":"Lost Stories","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have studied alchemy with the greatest masters, and my potions can produce wondrous effects. I am so drawn to knowledge that I neglect \nmy own safety.<h3>Gift</h3>At the beginning of each Scenario, you receive 3 Pharmaka \nTokens. Spend 1 Token when someone ingests one of your potions, then pick \none of the following effects:\n1. The subject transforms into an animal of your choice for the remainder of \nthe Scene. The person retains their human intelligence. \n2. The subject is in a confused state, which lowers their OL by 1 (or 1 Penalty in the case of a Hunter) for the rest of the Scene.\n3. The subject regains vitality and gains an Additional Wound that fades at \nthe end of the Scene.\nY ou are naturally resistant to your creations, and if you want to activate an \neffect on yourself, you must spend 1 Soma in addition to a Pharmaka Token. \nParticularly powerful subjects and Hunters may require you to perform \na Position Check before they suffer the effects of your potions. During an Interlude, or if you get your hands on valuable alchemical ingredients, you can \nrecover 1 Pharmaka Token.","notes":"Circe the Alchemist - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 20.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Circe the Alchemist","source":"Lost Stories"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"tYCbUnfubNs90MdZ","name":"Travel Companion","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Circe the Alchemist","source":"Lost Stories","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Eurylochus is my faithful servant pig and helps me with every task. He \nhas an almost human intelligence and one look is enough to understand \nus. I love him like a brother.<h3>Gift</h3>Eurylochus is a Minor NPC with the following profile:\nOL 5 Medium - (2 Wounds) \nDescriptor: I am Circe’s faithful pig servant and would do anything for her. \nEurylochus has always been your companion in experimentation, and over the \nyears he has been imbued with the power of Pharmaka. By spending 1 Soma, \nyou can activate one of the following effects:\n1. Human Form: Eurylochus takes the form of a handsome young man with \nflowing blond hair. He cannot speak but gains all the other advantages of a \nhuman body.\n2. Size Change: Eurylochus can shrink to the size of a mouse or grow to the \nsize of an elephant. The effect lasts for the duration of the Scene.\n3. Regeneration: Eurylochus will recover all of his Wounds, which can also \nbring him back into action if he is down to zero.","notes":"Circe the Alchemist - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 20.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Circe the Alchemist","source":"Lost Stories"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Z0tIcFM5Ac5fyCMh","name":"Collect Taxes","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Captain William of Nottingham","source":"Lost Stories","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a lawman and I am proud of my office. I have good \nleadership skills and know how to get those in charge to carry out \nan order. I like to be praised for my abilities.<h3>Gift</h3>At the end of each Scene, you receive 1 Taxes Token \nif you have discovered riches or secrets related to a location or NPC that \nyou can use to your advantage (at the Storyteller’s discretion). Y ou start \neach Scenario with 1 Taxes Token. At any time, you can spend 1 Taxes \nToken to activate one of these effects:\n1. Ask the Storyteller to reveal an NPC’s Gift or Equipment.\n2. Allow an ally to activate a Gift by replacing a special requirement or \nSoma cost.\n3. Confer 1 Additional Success to the action of an allied Hunter.","notes":"Captain William of Nottingham - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 22.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Captain William of Nottingham","source":"Lost Stories"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"ExI7nwk6NZDGm6Cs","name":"Lawman","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Captain William of Nottingham","source":"Lost Stories","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>Years of working as a bounty hunter have made me adept at \nhunting down and eliminating villains. When I am one step away \nfrom my goal, I do not consider retreating.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou can spend 1 Soma to assert your authority over \nordinary people. NPCs who recognize local authority will not try to \nharm you unless you act aggressively first. Even in cases of conflict, they \nwill avoid choosing you as a target unless you are the first to threaten \nthem. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success if you try to convince or intimidate \nsomeone who recognizes authority.","notes":"Captain William of Nottingham - bt-ls-hunters-sheets-1.2-eng-BASE-SCREEN.pdf, pages 22.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Captain William of Nottingham","source":"Lost Stories"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Ydgpvq9x31EhbRnP","name":"Diabolical Plan","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Moriarty the Gentleman Thief","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>My misdeeds have made me a real celebrity - I have clashed with \nheroes, nobles, and religious people, and I know how to deal with \neach of them. Sometimes I like to give my enemies a small \nadvantage just to make the challenge more interesting.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scenario, you can do each of the \nfollowing:\n1. Find a useful item (that you had previously planted) in your location. Receive 1 Spider Web Token.\n2. Deliver a message to someone without anyone else noticing. The \nmessage will be delivered during the Scene and, if you wish, you \nwill receive a reply at the beginning of the next Scene. Receive 1 \nSpider Web Token.\n3. Introduce an allied Minor NPC of yours to the Scene, who will be \nwilling to testify on your behalf. Receive 1 Spider Web Token.","notes":"Moriarty the Gentleman Thief - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Moriarty the Gentleman Thief","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"m4vtxMn0yFOQuZzN","name":"Dark Eminence","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Moriarty the Gentleman Thief","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am as ingenious in the use of concealed weapons and low blows \nas I am in plotting crime. The memory of my lost love has changed \nme deeply, and I try to prevent crime from creating innocent \nvictims.<h3>Gift</h3>Gain 1 Additional Success on all Checks involving \ndeception or obtaining something illegally. When you arrive at a new \nlocation, the Storyteller will reveal the possible presence of criminal \norganizations and their misdeeds. If you strike a beneficial pact with \na criminal or powerful organization, you will receive 1 Spider Web \nToken.","notes":"Moriarty the Gentleman Thief - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 2.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Moriarty the Gentleman Thief","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"0YCNZ6tWlHfbJs9J","name":"Cursed Blood","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Pale Medic","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have a certain amount of charm and I know how to put people at ease \nwith my polite manner. I feel uncomfortable in places where I have not \nbeen invited or where it is obvious that my presence is unwelcome.<h3>Gift</h3>Y our blood has incredible properties, so at the end of each \nScene, you recover 1 Wound; this can allow you to return even if you have \nno Wounds left. Self-inflict 1 Wound to draw your blood. Whoever drinks it \n(except you) can choose one of the following effects:\n1. Recover 1 Wound.\n2. Gain 1 Additional Success (increases OL by 1 in the case of an NPC) on \nall Checks for the rest of the Scene. For each Check in which this bonus \nis used, roll a die: if you roll a 5 or 6, the blood’s effect ends.","notes":"The Pale Medic - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 4.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"The Pale Medic","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"uBCfl8sWTWZ7evWJ","name":"Welcome to My House","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Pale Medic","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have vampire blood in me and my strength is far superior to that of \nan ordinary human. I am extremely sensitive to sunlight and try to \navoid it as much as possible.<h3>Gift</h3>If you care for an NPC, or are able to talk to them \nin a social setting, you gain 1 Additional Success on any Position Checks you \nmake to influence them. If the Check results in a Positive Outcome, you gain \n1 Additional Success on all Checks you make against that NPC for the rest of \nthe Scenario. After your conversation, the Storyteller will reveal something \nyou didn’t know about the NPC, such as part of their Agenda or a Gift you \nhaven’t seen in action.","notes":"The Pale Medic - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 4.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"The Pale Medic","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241687,"modifiedTime":1783973241687,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"eesYU9rJGswtGPiU","name":"Incognito Agents","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Respectable Mr. and Mrs. Mars","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>We are a harmless middle-aged couple and no one would ever consider \nus a danger. We are adept at going unnoticed. Our passion for human \nfood drives us to real binges.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou are considered a single Hunter, sharing Soma and \nWounds, and can act 2 times per Exchange. If you are separated, each of you \nwill receive 2 Penalties to any Checks you make alone. At the end of a Scene, \nyou can wipe others’ memory of your being there.","notes":"The Respectable Mr. and Mrs. Mars - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 6.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"The Respectable Mr. and Mrs. Mars","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"RLwTDbHFsEgpFNKy","name":"Informants","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"The Respectable Mr. and Mrs. Mars","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>We are always connected to the Mars Operations Center, and this \nallows us to have information about history and science. We are \nmorbidly attracted to any form of art because it is totally absent on our \nworld.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scene, you can ask for insight into an NPC, location, or \nevent that has occurred. The Storyteller will provide you with information useful \nto your objectives. Once per Scene, if you witness the unleashing of technology, \nan invention, or a magical power, you can report back to the Operations Center.","notes":"The Respectable Mr. and Mrs. Mars - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 6.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"The Respectable Mr. and Mrs. Mars","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"wgQ8nLzm4ofVm5HG","name":"Behold my Genius","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Doctor V. Frankenstein","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am a luminary in physics and medicine and know secrets that the \nbrightest academics can only dream of. I often get lost in my own \nreasoning, which I articulate aloud without realizing it.<h3>Gift</h3>By spending 1 Soma, you can use one of your \nfuturistic discoveries to generate an electric shock that inflicts 1 Wound. \nThe thunderbolt can strike up to twenty feet away and can change its \ntrajectory to avoid obstacles. Alternatively, you can spend 1 Soma to \ncharge an object with electricity, causing it to discharge when touched and \ninflicting 1 Wound. The object remains charged until the end of the Scene.","notes":"Doctor V. Frankenstein - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 8.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Doctor V. Frankenstein","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"c5Y2o7Euy2otPkpJ","name":"The Creature","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Doctor V. Frankenstein","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I always bring the Creature with me and know how to make the \nmost of its potential. There are times when the guilt of creating such \na monster brings me back to reality, and in those rare moments, I \ntry to do a good deed to atone for my sins.<h3>Gift</h3>Y our first creation is an NPC managed by the Storyteller, \nwith the following profile: \nOL Medium 5 - (4 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a powerful creature who feels no pain and has the strength \nof four men. My appearance is disgusting because of the many stitches that \nhold the pieces of my body together.\nAgenda: To be considered a person like any other and to find a family to take \nme in / I wish Victor to die, but as my creator, I cannot kill him with my own \nhands, and instead I try to facilitate his passing by acting indirectly.","notes":"Doctor V. Frankenstein - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 8.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Doctor V. Frankenstein","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"6aYw6G7l6pCyYpK3","name":"Blessing of the Defeated","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 5","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have a talent for assessing people’s merits and flaws, so I am good at \ncoordinating the efforts of those who trust me. I have a soft spot for those \nwho fail but try hard, and though I don’t like to admit it, sometimes the \ninstinct to help losers still takes over.<h3>Gift</h3>If your ally suffers a Wound or fails a Check, \nthey will gain 1 Additional Success (or increase their OL by 1 in the case \nof an NPC) on their next action. Alternatively, once per Scenario, you can \nchoose to have them recover 2 Soma or 1 Wound, or alternatively gain 2 XP . \nIf an NPC achieves their Agenda’s goal thanks to your help, you recover 1 \nSoma and gain 1 XP . \nI have a strong influence on people and my charm cannot be ignored.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 5 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 10.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 5","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"wyTN5lBLT62TUoYX","name":"The Lady’s Champion","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 5","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am very vain and love to waste time admiring my own image.<h3>Gift</h3>There’s always some fool who follows you around \nand proclaims themselves your Champion, until you lose all patience. The \nStoryteller creates an NPC with the following profile at the beginning of the \nScenario:\nOL Medium 5 - (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: A positive feature that identifies the identity and abilities of the \naspiring Champion. A Downside that identifies total devotion, obsession, love, \nor admiration for Vivienne of the Lake.\nAgenda: Help and protect Vivienne at all costs. Even if my lady tells me not to \nget in her way, I must do so to ensure her safety.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 5 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 10.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 5","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"KAEzCnLp1JNHlbYZ","name":"Porziella the Faithful Flea","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 6","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I learned some magic tricks from seven bandits, all of them brothers, \nand I know about arcane arts. I am attracted to magic and want to \ngather all knowledge about it.<h3>Gift</h3>Y our trusty flea follows you like a shadow. \nPorziella is an NPC under your full control with the following profile:\nOL Medium 5 - (3 Wounds)\nDescriptor: I am a flea the size of a dog, my skin is so hard and thick that not \neven a sword can pierce it.\nGift - Loyal Flea: Porziella always recognizes blood by its taste, which allows \nher to follow a trail or recognize who it belongs to without error. Once per \nScenario, Porziella can shield Viola by taking 1 Wound in her place. If she \ndoes this, she will be out of combat until the end of the Scene. If Porziella is \nnot present, Viola can spend 1 Soma to bring her into the Scene immediately, \novercoming all obstacles and impediments.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 6 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 12.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 6","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"xDwDg66BZsGN6ZaP","name":"The Magic of the Seven","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 6","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am courageous and stubborn. When I speak about justice and \nequality, the passion that animates me touches people’s hearts. For me, \nthe cause comes before everything and I am ready to take any action, \neven the most extreme.<h3>Gift</h3>Once per Scenario, you can use any of the \nfollowing powers, but you must have the appropriate Equipment.\n1. Mase’s Earring: It allows you to hear a speech even through a wall.\n2. Nardo’s Soap: Gives you 3 Additional Successes to free yourself from \nropes and chains, or to slip away. \n3. C ola’s Razor: Allows you to inflict 1 Additional Wound with one attack. \n4. Micco’s Staff: Plants sprout to block a passageway; the Storyteller creates a Threat that can absorb up to 3 Wounds before yielding. \n5. Petrullo’s Water: Creates a jet of water that strikes up to 30 feet but does \nno damage. \n6. Ascadeo’s Rock: It can be thrown and will fall exactly where you want it \nto fall, without causing any damage. \n7. Ceccone’s Crossbow: Grants you 2 Additional Successes when you \nshoot a dart.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 6 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 12.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 6","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"uXKhOUMgvGntCwgE","name":"Tiny","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 7","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have an unusual mind and remember every detail, even years \nlater. My body is puny and I hate to do strenuous work.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou know how to go unnoticed, so no one will ever pick you as \na direct target of one of their actions if there is at least one other Hunter \nin the Scene. Y ou can spend 1 Soma to leave a location without anyone \nnoticing, as long as there is at least one other Hunter to attract attention. \nY ou get 1 Additional Success on each Check where you can use your \ndiminutive stature, but you also get 1 Penalty on each Check where you \nhave to use brute force or physical strength.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 7 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 14.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 7","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"6se5s7Uyc4YaAqnx","name":"In the Right Place at the Right Time","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 7","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I have charisma to spare and I am a smooth talker who commands \nrespect and admiration. I must always have the last word.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou don’t get confused easily.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 7 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 14.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 7","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XKOAnE5QD6MzPy9d","name":"Hunting Companion","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 8","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>My senses are keen and my body is hardened by the outdoors. I hate \nbig cities, hustle and bustle, and generally can’t stand people who talk \ntoo much.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou don’t open your heart easily, but occasionally \nyou find companions you can trust. At the beginning of the Scenario, you \nchoose another Hunter as your hunting companion, who will receive 1 \nAdditional Success on all Defense Checks they make while you are in close \nproximity to cover their back. Y ou will always know where your hunting \ncompanion is and can spend 1 Soma to get to where they are, ignoring all \nobstacles. Y ou never speak and cannot express yourself verbally, but your \ncompanion will always clearly understand anything you try to tell them.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 8 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 16.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 8","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"oIdj0J7cgqVBmxzY","name":"Stalking","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 8","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am trained to kill all kinds of beasts and know how to use the \nhunting grounds to my advantage. Monsters must always be \ndestroyed, for them I see no mercy or redemption.<h3>Gift</h3>No prey can escape you, once per Scene you can find distinct \ntraces in a place or on an object. The Storyteller will reveal a useful piece of \ninformation of your choice: who left the clue, where it is, or a weakness in the \nobject. Y ou can spend 1 Soma to blend into your surroundings: as long as you \ndo not take any conspicuous actions (at the Storyteller’s discretion), Minor \nNPCs will not be able to see you, and you will get 3 Additional Successes on \nany Checks you make to go unnoticed or catch someone off guard.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 8 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 16.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 8","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"QFq2bXu7CaYIIcUa","name":"What I Want to See","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 9","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am used to walking around completely naked, so my physique is \ntough. I hate having unnecessary things on me, except for my beloved \ncrown.<h3>Gift</h3>If you see it, you can make it real. Y ou can spend 1 \nSoma and say what object you have in front of you. For the rest of the Scene, \nyou can use it as if it were real with all the characteristics it should have. Y ou \nget 1 Additional Success for each Check if you gain a genuine advantage due \nto the fact that others cannot see the object. Y ou can only have one object \ncreated by this Gift at a time. Y ou are completely immune to any effect based \non reducing or nullifying the ability to see.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 9 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 18.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 9","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"EMfv49SsdU4c9ypO","name":"What I Don’t Want to See","type":"gift","img":"systems/broken-tales/assets/icons/icon-gift.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 9","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives","category":"Lost Stories Gift"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Associated Descriptor</h3>I am good with words, I know etiquette, and I know how to dazzle the \ncrowd. I cannot refrain from commenting with the utmost sincerity \non the way my interlocutors dress.<h3>Gift</h3>Y ou start each Scene in the shadows, and \nas long as you are in this state, no one will notice your presence or the fact \nthat you are completely naked. As long as you do not perform actions that \nmake you the center of attention, you can continue to do whatever you want \nwithout anyone getting in the way, and you will never be singled out for \naction by a possible enemy. Subjects who base their perception on senses \nother than sight can easily detect you. When you perform a conspicuous \naction or decide to draw attention to yourself, you shift into the light. As \nlong as you are in this state, everyone will see you for what you really are. Y ou \nget 1 Additional Success on the first Check you make when you enter this \nstate. Y ou can spend 1 Soma at any time to return to the shadows.","notes":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 9 - Broken Tales - Lost Stories - Exclusive Pre-Gen Hunters.pdf, pages 18.","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"category":"Lost Stories Gift","owner":"Lost Stories Exclusives Hunter 9","source":"Lost Stories Exclusives"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241688,"modifiedTime":1783973241688,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
